* I'm just an in-between

733
01:03:40,050 --> 01:03:42,319
* I'm not a child

734
01:03:42,352 --> 01:03:44,955
* All children bore me

735
01:03:44,989 --> 01:03:47,124
* I'm not grown up

736
01:03:47,157 --> 01:03:49,393
* Grown-ups ignore me

737
01:03:49,426 --> 01:03:54,999
* And in every sense
I'm just on a fence *

738
01:03:55,032 --> 01:03:59,369
* I'm just an in-between *

739
01:04:02,239 --> 01:04:04,208
[ Girl ]
There's nothing
worse than a dope...

740
01:04:04,241 --> 01:04:06,977
who tries to look old
or sophisticated,

741
01:04:07,011 --> 01:04:10,080
so all the makeup we use
is just powder and lipstick.

742
01:04:10,114 --> 01:04:12,082
But we're fussy about lipstick.

743
01:04:12,116 --> 01:04:14,851
The right shade
can make or break.

744
01:04:23,961 --> 01:04:26,196
Of course clothes
are awfully important.

745
01:04:26,230 --> 01:04:29,633
If a girl doesn't dress right,
the way everyone else
is dressing,

746
01:04:29,666 --> 01:04:31,368
well, she's just out.

747
01:04:31,401 --> 01:04:34,071
She might as well be dead.

748
01:04:34,104 --> 01:04:36,240
I don't mean she needs
a lot of clothes,

749
01:04:36,273 --> 01:04:39,643
and they don't have
to be expensive,
but they have to be right,

750
01:04:39,676 --> 01:04:43,147
or she just labels herself
a crumb for life.

751
01:04:45,282 --> 01:04:46,616
What's this?

752
01:04:46,650 --> 01:04:48,018
What's what?

753
01:04:48,052 --> 01:04:52,156
Well, Jen, you're not
going to Emily's party
in those clothes, are you?

754
01:04:53,223 --> 01:04:55,425
Oh, Mother,
it's only a hen party.

755
01:04:55,459 --> 01:04:58,228
Do you want them to think
I'm different or something?

756
01:04:58,262 --> 01:05:00,164
Oh, all right.

757
01:05:00,197 --> 01:05:01,565
Bye.

758
01:05:01,598 --> 01:05:03,267
Be home early.

759
01:05:07,637 --> 01:05:12,309
[ American Girl ]
Before Pearl Harbor,
I was playing with paper dolls.

760
01:05:13,978 --> 01:05:16,580
After Pearl Harbor,

761
01:05:16,613 --> 01:05:19,349
I never played with dolls again.

762
01:05:22,519 --> 01:05:25,189
I'm part of the war effort now.

763
01:05:25,222 --> 01:05:27,391
[ Female Announcer ]
Workers for victory.

764
01:05:27,424 --> 01:05:31,695
The National Youth
Administration schooling
in skilled mechanical trades,

765
01:05:31,728 --> 01:05:33,363
and you earn while you learn.

766
01:05:33,397 --> 01:05:37,301
And note the nifty
new costumes too: blue jeans.

767
01:05:37,334 --> 01:05:39,736
So here's your chance
to take a slap at a Jap.

768
01:05:39,769 --> 01:05:42,239
The army of industry needs you.

769
01:05:50,780 --> 01:05:52,983
[ American Girl ]
I'm earning my own money.

770
01:05:55,619 --> 01:05:58,022
I'm not a little kid anymore.

771
01:06:01,225 --> 01:06:05,295
And I want to be treated
like an equal.

772
01:06:06,796 --> 01:06:09,666
I suppose you're
going out again tonight.

773
01:06:09,699 --> 01:06:11,468
Yeah.
So what?

774
01:06:11,501 --> 01:06:14,771
Jimmy, you have no business
staying out half the night...

775
01:06:14,804 --> 01:06:17,207
and coming home
all liquored up.

776
01:06:17,241 --> 01:06:21,045
Look, I'm getting
sick and tired
of being treated like a kid.

777
01:06:21,078 --> 01:06:23,180
I'm making
as much money as you are,

778
01:06:23,213 --> 01:06:25,549
and I have a right
to have a little fun.

779
01:06:29,419 --> 01:06:31,021
[ Door Slams ]

780
01:06:41,365 --> 01:06:43,367
[ American Girl ]
All the big businesses...

781
01:06:43,400 --> 01:06:45,602
were starting to understand
how important we were.

782
01:06:45,635 --> 01:06:50,040
We are endeavoring
to evaluate
your group's social habits.

783
01:06:50,074 --> 01:06:52,376
Could you tell us
in your own words?

784
01:06:53,643 --> 01:06:55,779
I can walk into a store...

785
01:06:55,812 --> 01:06:59,683
and buy clothes,
records, magazines...

786
01:06:59,716 --> 01:07:02,352
all aimed right at me.

787
01:07:02,386 --> 01:07:04,554
[ Male Announcer ]
Department stores,

788
01:07:04,588 --> 01:07:07,824
waking up to
the special market represented
by some six million girls...

789
01:07:07,857 --> 01:07:12,596
are earnestly concentrating
on giving this exacting
clientele what it wants.

790
01:07:15,699 --> 01:07:19,169
[ American Girl ]
We're the bosses
of the business now.

791
01:07:19,203 --> 01:07:21,538
A Big Bang.
Uh, chocolate--

792
01:07:21,571 --> 01:07:23,407
With chocolate sauce.
[ Man ]
Chocolate sauce.

793
01:07:23,440 --> 01:07:25,542
And, uh,
marshmallows, nuts.

794
01:07:25,575 --> 01:07:28,178
[ Girl ]
How about a cherry?
A cherry.

795
01:07:36,386 --> 01:07:38,322
[ American Girl ]
They called us subdebs.

796
01:07:40,224 --> 01:07:43,093
You'd see us
all over the magazines.

797
01:07:45,195 --> 01:07:47,431
We weren't debutantes at all.

798
01:07:49,133 --> 01:07:51,601
Just regular
old high school kids.

799
01:07:55,772 --> 01:07:58,208
But it sounded fancy.

800
01:07:58,875 --> 01:08:01,111
And we sure like fancy.

801
01:08:07,884 --> 01:08:11,321
I love being 17.

802
01:08:11,355 --> 01:08:14,491
I wish I could stay this age
for a while.

803
01:08:18,595 --> 01:08:22,832
Seventeen is that perfect spot
between adolescence--

804
01:08:22,866 --> 01:08:26,303
which means
you're going somewhere--

805
01:08:26,336 --> 01:08:30,574
and adulthood-- which means
you're on the downgrade.

806
01:08:33,643 --> 01:08:38,182
** [ Vocalizing ]

807
01:08:48,258 --> 01:08:50,327
Thank you very much,
ladies and gentlemen.

808
01:08:50,360 --> 01:08:55,499
[ Continues, Indistinct ]

809
01:08:57,801 --> 01:09:00,170
[ American Girl ]
Whether they
called us hooligans,

810
01:09:00,204 --> 01:09:04,708
flappers,
jitterbugs or subdebs,

811
01:09:04,741 --> 01:09:07,311
we knew who we were.

812
01:09:09,346 --> 01:09:11,648
The time had come...

813
01:09:11,681 --> 01:09:13,450
to declare it.

814
01:09:23,493 --> 01:09:26,296
[ British Boy ]
The article came out
in the New York Times.

815
01:09:27,831 --> 01:09:30,567
The Teen-Age Bill of Rights.

816
01:09:31,901 --> 01:09:33,737
A declaration.

817
01:09:33,770 --> 01:09:35,739
A manifesto.

818
01:09:35,772 --> 01:09:39,543
It was like a contract
between the generations.

819
01:09:41,478 --> 01:09:43,747
[ Male Announcer ]
From the beginning
of man's life on earth,

820
01:09:43,780 --> 01:09:48,385
there have been
but two generations:
the old and the young.

821
01:09:48,418 --> 01:09:51,288
And throughout
the world's history,

822
01:09:51,321 --> 01:09:53,523
in every nation
and in every time,

823
01:09:53,557 --> 01:09:55,292
the lives and fortunes
of the young...

824
01:09:55,325 --> 01:09:58,695
have been inevitably ruled
by the dictates of the old...

825
01:09:58,728 --> 01:10:03,433
who have called upon youth
to enforce their aims
and impose their will.

826
01:10:09,773 --> 01:10:11,408
Of all the world's youth,

827
01:10:11,441 --> 01:10:13,577
none are more fortunate
by birthright and inheritance...

828
01:10:13,610 --> 01:10:18,282
than the 21 million
boys and girls
between the ages of 16 and 24...

829
01:10:18,315 --> 01:10:21,485
who constitute one vast
and glamorous society.

830
01:10:39,569 --> 01:10:41,738
Today no one portion
of the American population...

831
01:10:41,771 --> 01:10:45,775
is more consistently admired
than its young men and women.

832
01:10:47,377 --> 01:10:49,946
For since the postwar days
of the flapper,

833
01:10:49,979 --> 01:10:51,748
speakeasy and flaming youth,

834
01:10:51,781 --> 01:10:54,951
America's youngsters have led
the styles and set the pace...

835
01:10:54,984 --> 01:10:57,521
for the young
of every other nation.

836
01:11:10,600 --> 01:11:14,270
[ British Boy ]
Each generation feels
that it is the future.

837
01:11:15,605 --> 01:11:17,374
[ American Boy ]
To the teenager,

838
01:11:17,407 --> 01:11:20,344
nothing is more important--

839
01:11:21,645 --> 01:11:24,581
[ German Girl ]
Than to find out
where we fit in...

840
01:11:24,614 --> 01:11:27,417
in relation to life around us.

841
01:11:29,085 --> 01:11:31,555
[ American Girl ]
It is a serious quest.

842
01:11:32,689 --> 01:11:34,290
Often a painful one.

843
01:11:38,428 --> 01:11:40,664
[ Explosion ]

844
01:11:44,934 --> 01:11:48,772
[ Male Announcer ]
Two atomic bombs
three days apart.

845
01:11:48,805 --> 01:11:50,874
Japan has surrendered.

846
01:11:50,907 --> 01:11:54,444
[ Cheering ]
And there's jubilation
around this earth.

847
01:12:00,984 --> 01:12:05,589
[ American Girl ]
This is a story
that ends with a beginning.

848
01:12:08,157 --> 01:12:10,727
The old world was over,

849
01:12:11,961 --> 01:12:14,564
and a new figure emerged.

850
01:12:15,131 --> 01:12:17,601
[ Laughing ]

851
01:12:24,841 --> 01:12:27,577
It would become
the model for youth...

852
01:12:27,611 --> 01:12:29,913
that still exists today.

853
01:12:31,481 --> 01:12:32,916
The teenager.

854
01:12:42,692 --> 01:12:45,795
[ German Girl ]
American culture kept
spreading around the world.

855
01:12:45,829 --> 01:12:47,897
[ Cheering ]

856
01:12:49,966 --> 01:12:52,502
They took away our weapons...

857
01:12:54,504 --> 01:12:57,407
and gave us Coca-Colas instead.

858
01:13:04,614 --> 01:13:07,617
[ British Boy ]
The teenager
was an American invention.

859
01:13:10,053 --> 01:13:11,555
It's what we wanted to be.

860
01:13:15,625 --> 01:13:17,727
We knew we could be
blown up in an instant.

861
01:13:20,063 --> 01:13:22,532
So we lived in the now.

862
01:13:24,801 --> 01:13:27,771
[ Chanting ]

863
01:13:29,105 --> 01:13:32,742
[ American Boy ]
Teenage was
a compromise solution.

864
01:13:34,243 --> 01:13:36,813
We got the freedom
we were looking for.

865
01:13:39,516 --> 01:13:41,785
But adults
still had some control.

866
01:13:46,823 --> 01:13:50,226
[ American Girl ]
A lot of people try
to shape the future.

867
01:13:50,259 --> 01:13:52,228
Parents, the government,

868
01:13:52,261 --> 01:13:54,998
bankers, the police.

869
01:13:57,266 --> 01:13:59,803
But it's the young ones
who will live in it.

870
01:14:01,004 --> 01:14:04,708
And we are the ones
who will fight for it.

